# Build context for the frontend image (ghcr.yml builds it with `context: .`).
# The FE only needs package*.json, the Next/TS config, src/ and public/ — everything
# below is reinstalled in the image, is runtime state, is a secret, or is the
# (vendored, Python) backend. Without this file the whole repo — including
# node_modules, .env.local and AI_KNOWLEDGE_LOG.md — is uploaded to the daemon.
#
# NOTE: the backend CI job uses `context: ./docker`, so this file does not apply
# to it; a context rooted at ./docker needs its own ./docker/.dockerignore.

# deps + build output (regenerated inside the image)
node_modules
.next
out
build
coverage

# the vendored Transformer Lab backend — Python, not part of the FE build
backend

# git + CI
.git
.github

# env + secrets — NEVER upload these into a build context
.env*

# runtime app data (may hold the HF token)
.rantai-data
.nqr-data

# the knowledge log carries live credentials
AI_KNOWLEDGE_LOG.md

# docker / docs / host scripts — not needed to build the FE
docker
docs
scripts
*.md
.DS_Store
*.pem
*.tsbuildinfo
npm-debug.log*
